## Problem 1 (Time Series Plots)

**Data:**

Housing is often a barometer for how people feel about the economy. Interest rates for mortgages are also the lowest of the interest rates for other personal borrowing.

Freddie Mac, a publicly traded government-sponsored enterprise focused on providing an affordable supply of mortgages across the US, shares the weekly average 30-year fixed mortgage rate. The average is over applications that week.

Details at <https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/MORTGAGE30US>

**Import & Wrangling:**

```{r}
#| warnings: false
#| output: false
#| code-fold: true
library(tidyverse)
library(scales)

rate <- read_csv("https://fred.stlouisfed.org/graph/fredgraph.csv?id=MORTGAGE30US")

# choose a better column name than FRED id
rate <- rate |>
  rename(Mortgage = MORTGAGE30US)
```

**EDA:**

Most recent observations:

```{r}
tail(rate, 8)
```

[***1(a). Make a time series plot of mortgage rates. Add meaningful axis labels and a title.***]{style="color:royalblue;"}

(A little bit of starter code is provided below, and the code chunk is set to not be evaluated with `eval: false` because the current code in there is not valid code and hence the document wouldn't render. Once you replace the code with valid code, set the chunk option to `eval: true`, or remove the `eval` option altogether since it's set to `true` by default.)

```{r}
#| eval: true

ggplot(rate, aes(x = DATE, y = Mortgage)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "Interest Rate",
       title = "A Simple Visual of Mortgage Rates in America")
```

[***1(b). Create a time series plot of mortgage rates since 2000. Add vertical lines to identify the election day of each US President and annotate the President's name.***]{style="color:royalblue;"}

```{r}
#| eval: true
election_dates <- ymd(c("2000-11-07", "2004-11-02", "2008-11-04", "2012-11-06", "2016-11-08", "2020-11-03"))
presidents <- c("George W. Bush", "George W. Bush", "Barack Obama", "Barack Obama", "Donald Trump", "Joe Biden")
ggplot(rate, aes(x = DATE, y = Mortgage)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    title = "Reflecting Mortgage Rates Since the Hanging Chad Crisis",
    x = "Year",
    y = "Interest Rate"
  ) +
  scale_x_date(limits = c(ymd("2000-11-07"), today())) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = as.numeric(election_dates), linetype = "dotted", color = "brown1") +
  annotate("text", x = election_dates, y = max(rate$Mortgage) * 0.73,label = presidents, angle = 90, vjust = -0.5, hjust = 0, size = 3.5)
```

