**Share:**

[***1(d). Prompt: What should someone know about the current mortgage rate compared to when you started high school?***]{style="color:royalblue;"}

Mortgage rates have fluctuated greatly. Fortunately for those viewing this graph seeking intrigue, it has been eight years since I first began high school. Rates were up and down and decreased heading a new decade, and plummeted when the global Covid-19 pandemic reached the United States. This was a fascinating revelation for me as most people I talk to about this topic blame Covid for the crash, but this clearly demonstrates that interest rates were declining for some time beforehand. However, the Atlanta Braves won the 2021 World Series and interest rates began to skyrocket. Can we say the two are related? Objectively, this is a prime example of spurious correlation, but I am a huge baseball fan and am somewhat fond of the Braves, so I'll concur with the statistical evaluation as it is quite convenient. However, my favorite team's rival won the 2020 World Series and I must say I am quite disappointed I could not blame the sharp increase in interest rates and subsequent problems associated with such on the LA Dodgers. Rates are beginning to come back down and it is neat to see in the graph that although the correlation is entirely spurious, the Texas Rangers won their first World Series in franchise history and rates began to decline once again. They still have yet to reach pre pandemic levels over a sustained period of time.

