## Problem 3 (Wrangling Data)

Utah is home to a collection of colleges and universities.

Data:

```{r}
#| code-fold: true
utah <- read_table("
name founded location type enrollment
BYU 1875 Provo Private 34499
UofU 1850 SLC Public 35310
UtahState 1888 Logan Public 28063
UVU 1941 Orem Public 44653
SUU 1897 CedarCity Public 15033
Weber 1889 Ogden Public 30536
UtahTech 1911 StGeorge Public 12567
Westminster 1875 SLC Private 1266
WGU 1996 Online Private 121437
Snow 1888 Ephraim Public 5900
SLCC 1948 SLC Public 26300
Ensign 1886 SLC Private 2200
MTECH 1989 Lehi Public 4034
")
```

```{r}
utah
```

[***#3(a). Who are the "big" schools?***]{style="color:royalblue;"}

Fill in the blanks for filtering `utah` where the `enrollment` is larger than 30,000.

```{r}
#| eval: true

utah |>
  filter(enrollment >= 30000)
```

[***#3(b). Who are the `Private` schools?***]{style="color:royalblue;"}

Fill in the blanks for filtering `utah` where the `type` is `Private`.

```{r}
#| eval: true

utah |>
  filter(type == "Private")
```

[***#3(c). Who are the schools located in Salt Lake City (`SLC`)? Report only the name of the schools.***]{style="color:royalblue;"}

Fill in the blanks for filtering `utah` appropriately and then pipe the result into `select` to produce a list of just the school names.

```{r}
#| eval: true

utah |>
  filter(location == "SLC") |>
  select(name)
```
